ng immigrants to England from the Low Countries in the 14th century, but failed to establish itself. Since the 19th century it has again been used occasionally in the English-speaking world, mostly among immigrants from Germanic countries."],"variants":[]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Loving’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"von","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Ronald .  It is sometimes used as a given name in its own right."],"variants":[{"name":"Ronald","meanings":["From the Old Norse personal name <i>Rögnvaldr</i> (composed of <i>regin</i> ‘advice, decision’ (also, ‘the gods’) + <i>valdr</i> ‘ruler’). This name was regularly used in the Middle Ages in northern England and Scotland, where Scandinavian influence was strong. It is now widespread throughout the English-speaking world."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"* Otto II von HOHENBERG was born as the son of Eberhard I Kirchberg and MRS Eberhard I von KIRCHBERG. He had at least 1 son with *E MRS Otto II von HOHENBERG. He died in 1189."},"et":{"–1189":"–1189","1111–1166":"1111–1166","–Female":"Surnud","–1183":"–1183","1083–Male":"1083–Surnud","1166–Female":"1166–Surnud","1189":"1189","1166":"1166","1111":"1111","1183":"1183","1083":"1083"},"fi":{"–1189":"–1189","1111–1166":"1111–1166","–Female":"Kuollut","–1183":"–1183","1083–Male":"1083–Kuollut","1166–Female":"1166–Kuollut","1189":"1189","1166":"1166","1111":"1111","1183":"1183","1083":"1083"},"fr":{"–1189":"–1189","1111–1166":"1111–1166","–Female":"Décédée","–1183":"–1183","1083–Male":"1083–Décédé","1166–Female":"1166–Décédée","1189":"1189","1166":"1166","1111":"1111","1183":"1183","1083":"1083","lifeSummary":"* Otto II von HOHENBERG est né, fils d’Eberhard I Kirchberg et MRS Eberhard I von KIRCHBERG. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec *E MRS Otto II von HOHENBERG. Il est déc